---
title: "Waiting on Stock"
---
The **Waiting on Stock** trigger initiates a flow when a customer signs up to be notified about a product that is currently out of stock.

- **Note:** This Trigger is a part of [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce) Integration

- **Topics covered:** -
- [How to Configure Waiting on Stock Trigger](#how-to-configure-waiting-on-stock-trigger)

- [Practical Example](#practical-example)

### How to Configure Waiting on Stock Trigger

While creating the Trigger Based Flows select **Waiting on Stock** trigger

![mceclip0.png](./images/mceclip0-28.png)

When setting up the **Waiting on Stock** trigger, you need to configure the following elements:- **Name:** Give the trigger a specific and meaningful name.

- **Description:** Write a brief summary that explains what the trigger does.

- **Select Store:** Choose the relevant BigCommerce Store that manages the product inventory.

- **Contact:** Indicate any specific criteria related to customer details or preferences.

- **BigCommerce:** Specify particular conditions related to the product.Once the configuration is completed, hit **Save**.

![mceclip1.png](./images/mceclip1-33.png)
